notificationGroup.name: notificationGroup
notificationGroup.description: Group containing all the notification types.

traps.name: traps
traps.description: Category containing all the traps. Each trap has sibling data nodes that contain the data associated with the most recently sent trap of that particular type. A GET-REQUEST sent to the WebMon for those data nodes will allow you to verify the data received in a recent trap.

analogInputs.name: analogInputs
analogInputs.description: Subtree containing trap and associated data for analog inputs. Analog inputs measure a value. The input always has a live reading, but traps are only sent on events, which are defined as the live reading crossing (or passing) one of the user-defined thresholds.

analogEventTrap.name: analogEventTrap
analogEventTrap.description: Notification sent upon an analog input reading crossing a threshold.

analogLiveLevel.name: analogLiveLevel
analogLiveLevel.description: The level associated with the analogLiveReading for this input.

analogLiveReading.name: analogLiveReading
analogLiveReading.description: The reading from the analog input described by analogInputDescription at the time the trap was sent. It is in the units described in analogUnitsOfMeasurement.

analogUnitsOfMeasurement.name: analogUnitsOfMeasurement
analogUnitsOfMeasurement.description: The units of measurement associated with the analogLiveReading.

analogLiveStateDescription.name: analogLiveStateDescription
analogLiveStateDescription.description: The description of the range in which the analogLiveReading is.

analogAlarmState.name: analogAlarmState
analogAlarmState.description: If true this field indicates the alarmed state. If false this field indicates the not alarmed state.

digitalInputs.name: digitalInputs
digitalInputs.description: Subtree containing trap and associated data for digital inputs. Digital inputs monitor a binary state. The input is always in one of two states. Traps are sent on events, which are defined as a change in the live state.

digitalEventTrap.name: digitalEventTrap
digitalEventTrap.description: Notification sent upon change of state on a digital input.

digitalLiveLevel.name: digitalLiveLevel
digitalLiveLevel.description: The level associated with digitalLiveState for this input.

digitalLiveState.name: digitalLiveState
digitalLiveState.description: The state of the digital input described by digitalInputDescription at the time the trap was sent.

digitalAlarmState.name: digitalAlarmState
digitalAlarmState.description: If true this field indicates the alarmed state. If false this field indicates the not alarmed state.

remoteDevices.name: remoteDevices
remoteDevices.description: Subtree containing trap and associated data for monitored remote devices. Remote devices are monitored for network connectivity. The device's live state is always either online or offline. Traps are sent on events, which are defined as a change in the live state.

remoteDeviceEventTrap.name: remoteDeviceEventTrap
remoteDeviceEventTrap.description: Notification sent upon change of state of a remote device.

remoteDeviceLiveState.name: remoteDeviceLiveState
remoteDeviceLiveState.description: The state of the remote device described by remoteDeviceDescription at the time the trap was sent. Online indicates connected, offline indicates not connected.

remoteDeviceAlarmState.name: remoteDeviceAlarmState
remoteDeviceAlarmState.description: If true this field indicates the alarmed state. If false this field indicates the not alarmed state.

faults.name: faults
